qas.question: Is the competition open to anyone?

answers.text: The competition is open to any club down to Level 10 of the English football league system
. All clubs in the top four levels (the Premier League and the three divisions of the Football League) are automatically eligible
Clubs in the next six levels (non-league football) are also eligible provided they have played in either the FA Cup, FA Trophy or FA Vase competitions
Newly formed clubs, such as F.C. United of Manchester in 2005–06 and also 2006–07, may not therefore play in the FA Cup in their first season.

qas.question: Do I need a stadium to compete?

answers.text: All clubs entering the competition must also have a suitable stadium.

plausible_answers.text: any club down to Level 10 of the English football league system

qas.question: Who is the competition closed to?

plausible_answers.text: All clubs in the top four levels

qas.question: What season can newly formed clubs start playing in?
What does a club not need in order to play?

plausible_answers.text: the FA Cup, FA Trophy or FA Vase
